						<summary>

						<p>A pillar in the Śelliyammaṉ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">No king: Śaka [9]82 = 1060 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and the date does not seem to be genuine. It records a gift of a <hi rend="italic">nandā</hi> lamp to the image of the god Aḻagiyama[ṇa]vāḷa set up in the temple of the god Mahāvishṇu Kalikēsariviṇṇagar-āḷvār of the village of Vikkiramachōḻa-charuppēdimaṅgalam, by a certain Brāhmaṇa woman, wife of Prayāgai-Sūryyadēvan, a member of the executive council <hi rend="italic">(Āḷuṅgaṇam)</hi> of the place. The record also makes mention of the <hi rend="italic">sabhai</hi> of the village, who had undertaken to burn the <hi rend="italic">nandā</hi> lamp.</p>						

						</summary>
